FBIS3-25258 "drafr030_c_94020" FBIS-AFR-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA ANC Opposes Development of Country's Nuclear Capability MB1202150094 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 1100 GMT 12 Feb 94 MB1202150094 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The African National Congress [ANC] of South Africa has stated unambiguously that it does not want a nuclear capability in South Africa. The head of the ANC's department of economic planning, Mr. Trevor Manuel, says the ANC has endorsed the Organization of African Unity's decision calling for the African continent to be a nuclear weapons free zone. Mr. Manuel was speaking in Cape Town at [words indistinct], he said the ANC held the view that a [word indistinct].
